OL,3,CWelfare concessions to be set out
OL,4,Cahead of crunch vote
OL,6,FThe Work and Pensions Secretary said:
OL,7,F"We must build a welfare system that
OL,8,Fprovides security for those who cannot
OL,9,Fwork and the right support for those
OL,10,Fwho can. Too often, disabled people
OL,11,Ffeel trapped, worried that if they try
OL,12,Fto work, they could lose the support
OL,13,Fthey depend on.
OL,15,F"That is why we are taking action to
OL,16,Fremove those barriers, support
OL,17,Fdisabled people to live with dignity
OL,18,Fand independence, and open routes into
OL,19,Femployment for those who want to
OL,20,Fpursue it.
