OL,6,FVicky Foxcroft, who quit as a Labour
OL,7,Fwhip over the reforms, told The
OL,8,FGuardian there were "areas where I
OL,9,Fstill think there's need for movement"
OL,10,Fand that she had not decided how to
OL,11,Fvote.
OL,13,FOlivia Blake, a Labour MP with a
OL,14,Fdisclosed disability, told the paper
OL,15,Fthe changes could create "an unethical
OL,16,Ftwo-tier system that treats two people
OL,17,Fwith the exact same injury or illness
OL,18,Fdifferently".
