OL,6,FThe Liberal Democrats plan to vote
OL,7,Fagainst and have called for the
OL,8,FGovernment to speed up access-to-work
OL,9,Fdecisions to help people enter the
OL,10,Fworkforce.
OL,12,FDeputy leader Daisy Cooper said:
OL,13,F"Liberal Democrats simply cannot
OL,14,Fsupport any measures that make things
OL,15,Fharder for unpaid carers, disabled
OL,16,Fpeople who rely on support with daily
OL,17,Ftasks in order to stay employed, and
OL,18,Fthose whose disabilities mean that
OL,19,Fthey will never be able to work.
